617
00:29:11,800 --> 00:29:13,833
- Drop and give me 20, dogmeat!

618
00:29:13,833 --> 00:29:15,867
(Gary sighs)

619
00:29:15,867 --> 00:29:18,967
(sad music)

620
00:29:18,967 --> 00:29:21,467
(light music)

621
00:29:22,700 --> 00:29:25,067
This is a Special
Forces climbing harness,

622
00:29:25,067 --> 00:29:27,733
used in insertion and
 extraction of troops.

623
00:29:27,733 --> 00:29:29,233
- No problemo.

624
00:29:29,233 --> 00:29:31,067
- Piece of cake.

625
00:29:31,067 --> 00:29:33,133
- Born climbing.

626
00:29:33,133 --> 00:29:34,700
- Well let's do it.

627
00:29:36,433 --> 00:29:37,833
- Well what do you think?

628
00:29:37,833 --> 00:29:41,133
(wacky music)

629
00:29:41,133 --> 00:29:42,967
- I think if you've mastered
 the art of rappelling

630
00:29:42,967 --> 00:29:45,067
you'll not have this
 kind of problem again.

631
00:29:45,067 --> 00:29:46,067
- What are you
 talking about problem,

632
00:29:46,067 --> 00:29:47,433
what's wrong with this?

633
00:29:47,433 --> 00:29:48,233
- Well look at you, you're
 hanging upside down,

634
00:29:48,233 --> 00:29:49,167
for crying out loud.

635
00:29:49,167 --> 00:29:50,400
- 'Cause I'm supposed to be!

636
00:29:50,400 --> 00:29:51,333
- This is not how
 it's supposed to be,

637
00:29:51,333 --> 00:29:52,267
if this was a real situation,

638
00:29:52,267 --> 00:29:53,533
you'd be a dead man by now.

639
00:29:53,533 --> 00:29:54,200
You got that?
 - [Andrew] I'm ready, alright?

640
00:29:54,200 --> 00:29:55,067
I'm ready to go.

641
00:29:55,067 --> 00:29:55,900
Let's go.

