1333
01:08:14,233 --> 01:08:16,600
(Valerie chuckles)

1334
01:08:16,600 --> 01:08:18,533
- It's my fault, I slipped up.

1335
01:08:18,533 --> 01:08:21,067
- No, you couldn't
 have done anything.

1336
01:08:21,067 --> 01:08:22,767
Now we just have
to get him back.

1337
01:08:22,767 --> 01:08:23,600
- But how?

1338
01:08:25,333 --> 01:08:27,733
- We have a bargaining chip.

1339
01:08:27,733 --> 01:08:29,133
Just need a plan.

1340
01:08:31,467 --> 01:08:33,900
- Okay, we've gotta
 get out of here.

1341
01:08:33,900 --> 01:08:35,633
Simon plans to
 release game tonight,

1342
01:08:35,633 --> 01:08:37,667
it has amazing mind
 control properties.

1343
01:08:37,667 --> 01:08:39,300
It's a mental virus.

1344
01:08:39,300 --> 01:08:41,800
- We'll stop them, Andrew
 has part of the launch code.

1345
01:08:41,800 --> 01:08:43,667
- No, that'll just
 slow him down.

1346
01:08:43,667 --> 01:08:45,067
We need to destroy the mainframe

1347
01:08:45,067 --> 01:08:47,600
before he goes online tonight.

1348
01:08:47,600 --> 01:08:49,833
- Then there's no
 way into the system.

1349
01:08:49,833 --> 01:08:51,200
- [Valerie] None.

1350
01:08:51,200 --> 01:08:54,200
(hopeful music)
 - Wait, I've got it!

1351
01:08:54,200 --> 01:08:56,233
It's like the urban legend.

1352
01:08:56,233 --> 01:08:57,167
- What do you mean?

1353
01:08:57,167 --> 01:08:59,433
- I know how to stop Simon.

1354
01:09:01,100 --> 01:09:04,767
(moves into dramatic music)

1355
01:09:05,933 --> 01:09:08,833
- Well, you wanted
 to be game testers,

1356
01:09:09,967 --> 01:09:13,267
I guess you can be
 the first test pilots.

1357
01:09:13,267 --> 01:09:15,167
- You're insane.

1358
01:09:15,167 --> 01:09:16,667
- The world is
 changing every day,

1359
01:09:16,667 --> 01:09:18,333
we must change with it.

1360
01:09:18,333 --> 01:09:20,833
I've enjoyed our
 relationship, Valerie.

1361
01:09:20,833 --> 01:09:23,833
(telephone rings)

1362
01:09:23,833 --> 01:09:25,300
- Call for you.

1363
01:09:25,300 --> 01:09:26,833
- Right on time.

1364
01:09:26,833 --> 01:09:28,067
- Andrew.

1365
01:09:28,067 --> 01:09:29,100
- Yeah, Simon.

1366
01:09:29,100 --> 01:09:30,533
I have a deal to offer you.

1367
01:09:30,533 --> 01:09:31,633
- I'm listening.

1368
01:09:31,633 --> 01:09:34,467
- Your disk for the girls.

1369
01:09:34,467 --> 01:09:36,067
- Disk for the girls?

1370
01:09:36,067 --> 01:09:37,333
- Don't do it, Andrew!

1371
01:09:37,333 --> 01:09:39,667
Remember the snake that
bit the guy in the butt.

1372
01:09:39,667 --> 01:09:40,500
- Cute.

1373
01:09:42,267 --> 01:09:44,567
You bring me the disk,
I'll give you the girls.

1374
01:09:44,567 --> 01:09:46,467
- I'm not coming to you.

1375
01:09:46,467 --> 01:09:49,067
- Very well, where are we
 going to do the exchange?

1376
01:09:49,067 --> 01:09:50,867
- Front of my house, tonight.

1377
01:09:50,867 --> 01:09:53,800
- Alone, no police,
 and no friends.

1378
01:09:54,933 --> 01:09:55,767
- Alone.

1379
01:09:58,767 --> 01:10:02,567
- I can't think of a better
 place to launch Mind Chaser.

1380
01:10:02,567 --> 01:10:04,433
I'm afraid you're
 gonna have to wait.

1381
01:10:04,433 --> 01:10:07,900
I don't want to show
 up with damaged goods.

1382
01:10:07,900 --> 01:10:09,767
(scary screeching music)

1383
01:10:09,767 --> 01:10:10,967
- Why would Cat mention the guy

1384
01:10:10,967 --> 01:10:12,800
that got bit on the
 butt by a snake?

1385
01:10:12,800 --> 01:10:14,133
- Bit on the butt?

1386
01:10:14,133 --> 01:10:15,233
By a snake?

1387
01:10:15,233 --> 01:10:16,700
- You know the urban legend?

1388
01:10:16,700 --> 01:10:19,500
- Wait a minute, I know
 what she was talking about.

1389
01:10:19,500 --> 01:10:20,800
I have a plan.

1390
01:10:20,800 --> 01:10:23,467
(loud chirping)

1391
01:10:31,633 --> 01:10:34,300
(intense music)

1392
01:10:39,667 --> 01:10:40,867
- Go on, out.

1393
01:10:40,867 --> 01:10:42,033
(Rocky barks)

1394
01:10:42,033 --> 01:10:42,867
- Stay.

1395
01:10:42,867 --> 01:10:43,700
(Rocky barks)

1396
01:10:43,700 --> 01:10:44,533
Stay.

1397
01:10:49,800 --> 01:10:51,367
- Where's the disk?

1398
01:10:52,967 --> 01:10:54,333
- It's right here, Simon.

1399
01:10:54,333 --> 01:10:55,200
- Toss it here.

1400
01:10:55,200 --> 01:10:56,367
- Don't do it!

1401
01:11:01,900 --> 01:11:03,700
- Where's that idiot Bill?

1402
01:11:03,700 --> 01:11:05,067
- Who, Mr. Westbourne?

1403
01:11:05,067 --> 01:11:07,333
- The computer nerd, Bill!

1404
01:11:07,333 --> 01:11:10,267
(car brakes loudly)

1405
01:11:10,267 --> 01:11:11,300
(Rocky barks)

1406
01:11:11,300 --> 01:11:13,367
- My dad's mailbox.

1407
01:11:13,367 --> 01:11:15,400
Now you guys are
 really in trouble.

1408
01:11:15,400 --> 01:11:17,067
- Sorry I'm late, car trouble.

1409
01:11:17,067 --> 01:11:17,933
- So I see.

1410
01:11:24,067 --> 01:11:25,833
- This is the right disk.

1411
01:11:25,833 --> 01:11:27,667
- Clever boy.

1412
01:11:27,667 --> 01:11:29,700
Check it for viruses.

1413
01:11:29,700 --> 01:11:31,633
(loud beeping)

1414
01:11:31,633 --> 01:11:35,800
- The disk is cleared, no
 viruses, no trojan horses.

1415
01:11:36,733 --> 01:11:38,400
- Send it to the mainframe.

1416
01:11:38,400 --> 01:11:40,133
Let's get this show started.

1417
01:11:40,133 --> 01:11:41,233
- Oh, I'll need your access code

1418
01:11:41,233 --> 01:11:43,167
to enter the mainframe.

1419
01:11:50,067 --> 01:11:51,400
- It's showtime.

1420
01:11:52,400 --> 01:11:54,533
- [Voiceover] Access granted.

1421
01:11:54,533 --> 01:11:56,167
- What are you doing?

1422
01:11:56,167 --> 01:11:57,600
- Simon,

1423
01:11:57,600 --> 01:11:59,200
I couldn't figure
 out what Cat meant

1424
01:11:59,200 --> 01:12:01,200
when she mentioned the snake,

1425
01:12:01,200 --> 01:12:02,767
but then it came to me.

1426
01:12:02,767 --> 01:12:04,400
See, Simon, when your
 computer's connected

1427
01:12:04,400 --> 01:12:08,067
to the Internet, it's like a
 toilet connected to the sewer.

1428
01:12:08,067 --> 01:12:11,900
And when your garbage
goes out, we can get in.

1429
01:12:11,900 --> 01:12:12,733
(mischievous music)
And just like the snake

1430
01:12:12,733 --> 01:12:15,267
that bit the man's butt,

1431
01:12:15,267 --> 01:12:16,700
I can bite yours.

1432
01:12:16,700 --> 01:12:21,067
- You can't access my
 mainframe without my codes.

1433
01:12:21,067 --> 01:12:23,200
- That's true, but we
 have your code now.

1434
01:12:23,200 --> 01:12:25,467
You just gave it to us.

1435
01:12:25,467 --> 01:12:28,300
(whimsical music)

1436
01:12:33,533 --> 01:12:36,067
(Rocky barks)

1437
01:12:38,800 --> 01:12:40,533
- This can't be!

1438
01:12:40,533 --> 01:12:42,067
(loud beeps)

1439
01:12:42,067 --> 01:12:43,700
You're in my system.

1440
01:12:44,700 --> 01:12:45,967
- You wanna play a game, Simon?

1441
01:12:45,967 --> 01:12:46,800
Play ours!

1442
01:12:49,533 --> 01:12:52,500
(energetic music)
 Land holdings in Asia.

1443
01:12:52,500 --> 01:12:55,333
(loud beeps)
 Gone.

1444
01:12:57,100 --> 01:12:58,200
Looks like you have
 offshore accounts

1445
01:12:58,200 --> 01:13:00,267
for one billion dollars.

1446
01:13:01,167 --> 01:13:03,300
(loud beeps)

1447
01:13:03,300 --> 01:13:04,267
Gone.

1448
01:13:04,267 --> 01:13:06,767
- You can't ruin me.

1449
01:13:06,767 --> 01:13:08,767
(loud beeps)

1450
01:13:08,767 --> 01:13:11,500
- US Treasury certificates.

1451
01:13:11,500 --> 01:13:13,100
What do you think Gary,

1452
01:13:13,100 --> 01:13:17,133
you need six million
 in negotiable US
 Treasury certificates?

1453
01:13:17,133 --> 01:13:18,933
- Donate it to save the whales.

1454
01:13:18,933 --> 01:13:20,167
- Hey, you know what?

1455
01:13:20,167 --> 01:13:22,067
Let's just erase
 the whole empire.

1456
01:13:22,067 --> 01:13:23,233
(loud beeps)

1457
01:13:23,233 --> 01:13:27,067
(loud continuous explosions)

1458
01:13:33,400 --> 01:13:36,267
Bankrupt Simon, it's over.

1459
01:13:36,267 --> 01:13:37,300
You've lost.

1460
01:13:37,300 --> 01:13:38,133
(police sirens wailing)

1461
01:13:38,133 --> 01:13:39,567
You have nothing.

1462
01:13:51,800 --> 01:13:54,067
- Simon, you're under arrest.

1463
01:13:54,067 --> 01:13:56,733
(dramatic music)

1464
01:13:58,133 --> 01:14:01,367
(gun is cocked loudly)

1465
01:14:02,733 --> 01:14:05,200
(Rocky barks)

1466
01:14:05,200 --> 01:14:07,767
- You may have ruined me,

1467
01:14:07,767 --> 01:14:09,567
but I'm not giving
 up that easily.

1468
01:14:09,567 --> 01:14:10,933
- Don't do it.

1469
01:14:10,933 --> 01:14:12,733
- You stay where you are.

1470
01:14:12,733 --> 01:14:13,667
(Rocky barks)

1471
01:14:13,667 --> 01:14:14,833
- It's time to give up, Simon.

1472
01:14:14,833 --> 01:14:16,167
- Wrong, Andrew.

1473
01:14:17,100 --> 01:14:17,933
(loud gunshot)

1474
01:14:17,933 --> 01:14:21,100
(Rocky wails in pain)

1475
01:14:26,733 --> 01:14:27,567
- Rocky?

1476
01:14:33,067 --> 01:14:33,833
Rocky?

1477
01:14:35,600 --> 01:14:37,133
(sad music)
 You need to get up.

1478
01:14:37,133 --> 01:14:38,300
Get up, Rocky.

1479
01:14:43,133 --> 01:14:46,700
Rocky, get up boy. (cries)

1480
01:14:50,667 --> 01:14:52,067
Don't die, Rocky.

1481
01:14:58,100 --> 01:14:59,567
Help.

1482
01:14:59,567 --> 01:15:00,433
- Rocky.

1483
01:15:06,767 --> 01:15:07,800
(Rocky barks)

1484
01:15:07,800 --> 01:15:08,633
- Rocky!

1485
01:15:08,633 --> 01:15:10,400
(energetic music)

1486
01:15:10,400 --> 01:15:12,767
Rocky. (laughs)

1487
01:15:12,767 --> 01:15:15,067
- The cyber suit,
 it's bullet proof.

1488
01:15:15,067 --> 01:15:15,867
- Rocky!

1489
01:15:17,733 --> 01:15:18,567
Oh god.

1490
01:15:20,367 --> 01:15:21,900
- Attaboy, Rocky.

1491
01:15:21,900 --> 01:15:22,733
- Rocky!

1492
01:15:23,633 --> 01:15:25,533
Oh, good boy, good boy!

1493
01:15:27,367 --> 01:15:28,767
- Beaten by kids.

1494
01:15:30,067 --> 01:15:31,733
- Not just any kids.

1495
01:15:36,067 --> 01:15:40,233
- (sighs in relief)
 Rocky saved my life.

1496
01:15:40,233 --> 01:15:43,267
(Rocky barks)

1497
01:15:43,267 --> 01:15:44,100
And you.

1498
01:15:45,533 --> 01:15:48,533
You're pretty amazing yourself.

1499
01:15:48,533 --> 01:15:51,133
Were you always
 this amazing, Cat?

1500
01:15:51,133 --> 01:15:52,233
(optimistic music)

1501
01:15:52,233 --> 01:15:53,067
Catherine.

1502
01:15:53,933 --> 01:15:56,867
(Catherine laughs)

1503
01:16:01,633 --> 01:16:04,233
(Simon groans)

1504
01:16:06,800 --> 01:16:09,067
- This is a top secret
 government project.

1505
01:16:09,067 --> 01:16:13,067
Your son's a hero, but you
 can't tell anyone about it.

1506
01:16:13,067 --> 01:16:14,967
- My mailbox!

1507
01:16:14,967 --> 01:16:17,100
- Everything will be
 back in order by dawn.

1508
01:16:17,100 --> 01:16:18,533
Better than ever.

1509
01:16:21,067 --> 01:16:22,833
(Mrs. Henderson gasps)

1510
01:16:22,833 --> 01:16:25,333
(happy music)

1511
01:16:33,067 --> 01:16:37,200
- And this is the last
 remaining copy of the game.

1512
01:16:40,967 --> 01:16:43,400
(loud beeps)
 (roaring thunder)

1513
01:16:43,400 --> 01:16:45,433
Anybody wanna play Mind Chaser?

1514
01:16:45,433 --> 01:16:47,333
- [Catherine And Gary] Not.

1515
01:16:47,333 --> 01:16:48,433
(loud beeps)

1516
01:16:48,433 --> 01:16:50,167
- [Voiceover] Disk erased.

1517
01:16:50,167 --> 01:16:52,533
You have a virtual caller.

1518
01:16:52,533 --> 01:16:53,900
- Oh.
 - [Catherine] Uh oh.

1519
01:16:53,900 --> 01:16:56,367
- [Andrew] Send it through.

1520
01:16:56,367 --> 01:16:59,367
- Andrew, Catherine,
 Gary and Rocky.

1521
01:17:00,467 --> 01:17:01,767
(Rocky barks)

1522
01:17:01,767 --> 01:17:03,967
I have a mission for you,

1523
01:17:03,967 --> 01:17:06,133
if you choose to accept it.

1524
01:17:06,133 --> 01:17:09,433
(dramatic music)

1525
01:17:09,433 --> 01:17:12,067
(Rocky barks)

1526
01:17:12,067 --> 01:17:15,767
(moves into energetic music)

1527
01:20:08,933 --> 01:20:11,767
(MultiCom Jingle)

